_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/763973/c-inconsistant-label-indentation-when-formatting.html)._

---
Formatting a section or document which contains labels can result in inconsistant indentation of labels. If a label followed a non-bracketed if statement, the label will be indented further than if it follows a a bracketed if statement

Sample 1:

```csharp
    void Foo()
    {
        if (true)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("True");
        }

    Cleanup:
        // Do Cleanup
        return;
    }
```

Sample 2:

```csharp
    void Bar()
    {
        if (true)
            Console.WriteLine("True");

        Cleanup:
        // Do Cleanup
        return;
    }
```

