### Original Solutions
(no solutions)

Imagine if you have the following generic struct definition:

```c#
public struct Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>
        where TPart1 : struct, IPart<T1>
        where TPart2 : struct, IPart<T2>
        where TPart3 : struct, IPart<T3>
        where TPart4 : struct, IPart<T4>
    {

        // ... some code here

        private static readonly Func<
            Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>,
            Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>>[] Modifiers = GetModifiers().ToArray();

        private static IEnumerable<Func<Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>, Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>>> GetModifiers()
        {
            return Modifier.GetModifiers<Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>>(
                // ... some code here
            );
        }
```

If we could refer to the current closed type definition, code would be much more readable, for example by using Self:
```c#
public struct Identifier<TPart1, TPart2, TPart3, TPart4, T1, T2, T3, T4>
        where TPart1 : struct, IPart<T1>
        where TPart2 : struct, IPart<T2>
        where TPart3 : struct, IPart<T3>
        where TPart4 : struct, IPart<T4>
    {

        // ... some code here

        private static readonly Func<Self, Self>[] Modifiers = GetModifiers().ToArray();

        private static IEnumerable<Func<Self,Self>> GetModifiers()
        {
            return Modifier.GetModifiers<Self>(
                // ... some code here
            );
        }
```

If you believe it could be useful I would be happy to make a PR. I would need some guidance.

**Version Used**: Visual Studio Community 2019 Preview v16.4.0 preview 1.0

**Steps to Reproduce**:
1. Check `.NET Core 3.0 SDK` in the Individual Components section of the installer
2. Compile this .NET Core console program:
```csharp
class Program
{
    public interface Iface { }
    static Iface GetImpl() => null;
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        var impl = GetImpl();

        if (impl != default)
        {

        }
    }
}
```

