**Steps to Reproduce**:
```C#
class Program
{
    enum E { a, b, c }

    static int Main()
    {
        E e = E.a;

        if (e == E.a)
            return e switch
            {
                E.a => 0
            };

        switch (e)
        {
            case E.a:
            case E.b:
                return e switch
                {
                    E.a => 0,
                    E.b => 1
                };
        }

        return e switch
        {
            E.a => 0
        };

        // unreachable
        return 0;
    }
}
```

**Expected Behavior**: no warnings (or at least not on the first two)

**Actual Behavior**: CS8509 for all switch expression

At minimum, "the switch expression does not handle all possible inputs" is simply not true.

